               <p>335. <persName id="def1-335-18510106" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-335-18510106" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-335-18510106" type="age" value="25"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-335-18510106" type="surname" value="LARMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-335-18510106" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">GEORGE LARMAN</hi>
                  </persName>. was indicted<rs id="t18510106-335-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18510106-335-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18510106-335-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp> for a like offence.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. ELLIS</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">BODKIN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510106-name-42" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-42" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-42" type="surname" value="BLAKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-42" type="given" value="SUSAN"></interp>SUSAN BLAKE</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband keeps a beer-shop, in Colt-lane, Bethnal-green. On 22nd Dec. the prisoner came for half a pint of beer, about half-past two o'clock in the afternoon—he gave me a half-sovereign—I showed it to my husband—it was a bad one—he came and asked the prisoner if he was aware it was bad—he said, "No"—he then paid me with a penny.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510106-name-43" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-43" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-43" type="surname" value="BLAKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-43" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BLAKE</persName>
                  </hi>. My wife showed me the half-sovereign—I considered it bad—I said to the prisoner, "Did you give this half-sovereign?"—he said, "Yes"—I said, "Are you aware it is bad?"—he said, "No"—he said he took it of Mr. Burford, a man who goes about with greens and other things—I said, "Come with me to Mr. Burford's"—we went on, and in going along, I said I thought he had known it was bad, and a man who was with me went for a policeman—I asked the prisoner if he had any more about him—he put his band into his pocket, and pulled out a had sovereign—I gave him, and the sovereign and half-sovereign, to the officer.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510106-name-44" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-44" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-44" type="surname" value="WINTGEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-44" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES WINTGEN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, K</hi> 301). The prisoner was given to me, and this sovereign and half-sovereign.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510106-name-45" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-45" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-45" type="surname" value="WEBSTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-45" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WEBSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to the Royal Mint. These are both counterfeit.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi> I took them both for articles I had sold; I was not aware they were bad.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18510106-name-46" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-46" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-46" type="surname" value="BLAKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18510106-name-46" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BLAKE</persName>
                  </hi>. <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> The prisoner said he would go with me to Burford's; and in going along, he said he was a stranger, and he did</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185101060014"></xptr>
               <p>not know where Burford lived—when he got to the station, he said he took the sovereign and half-sovereign at market, before daylight, on the Saturday morning. (<hi rend="italic">The prisoner received a good character</hi>)</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18510106-335-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18510106-335-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18510106-335-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>
                     <hi rend="smallCaps">GUILTY</hi>. Aged 25.—<hi rend="italic">Recommended to mercy by the Jury</hi>
                  </rs>.—
<rs id="t18510106-335-punishment-14" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18510106-335-punishment-14" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
